FBIS4-8490 "dreeu072_y_94006" FBIS-EEU-94-072 Daily Report 13 Apr 1994 YUGOSLAVIA Federal Government Withdraws AFP, CNN Accreditations Government Withdraws AFP, CNN Accreditations AU1304184794 Paris AFP in English 1823 GMT 13 Apr 94 AU1304184794 Paris AFP English BFN [Excerpts] Belgrade, April 13 (AFP) -- The Yugoslav government officially withdrew press accreditations from AFP correspondents here Wednesday [13 April], accusing them of waging a "media war" against Belgrade. The information ministry withdrew accreditations from bureau chief Nicolas Miletitch and three other journalists to cover events in Serbia and Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM], but not for Serb-held areas of Croatia and Bosnia. On Tuesday the ministry accused AGENCE FRANCE-PRESSE and Cable News Network (CNN) of "waging a merciless media war against Yugoslavia, from its territory." [passage omitted] The AFP journalists whose accreditation was withdrawn can continue to coordinate coverage of events in Macedonia and Albania.
